'''Taung''' is a small [[town]] situated in the [[North West Province (South Africa)|North West Province]] of [[South Africa]]. The name means ''place of the lion'' and was named after Tau, the chief of the [[Tswana language|Tswana]] speaking Legoya or BaTaung tribe. ''Tau'' is the Tswana word for [[lion]].
